The ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) has eulogised its immediate past National Chairman, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole for dedicating his life to the service of humanity. Chairman, Caretaker Extra-Ordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) and Yobe Governor, Mai Mala Buni, in a statement in Abuja to mark the 69th birthday of the former party leader said, Oshiomole has distinguished himself as a labour leader, governor and party leader. The statement reads: “The All Progressives Congress (APC) heartily felicitates with H.E. Comrade Adams Aliyu Oshiomhole on his 69th birthday anniversary on Sunday April 4th, 2021. “Comrade Oshiomhole has always dedicated his life to the service of humanity as a labour leader, as a governor and as National Chairman of Nigeria’s ruling political party, the APC. “The entire APC family joins Comrade Oshiomhole, his family and associates to celebrate this gift of good life. “We pray to God Almighty to bless Comrade Oshiomhole with many more years, good health, wisdom and strength to continue serving humanity.”